
[1]skill

   SKILL, n. Calleo, that is to strain, stretch, reach, and with to
   perfect, that is, to make sound, or to reach the utmost limit. The
   sense of folly, error, sin, preverseness, is from wandering, deviation.

   1. The familiar knowledge of any art or science, united with readiness
   and dexterity in execution or performance, or in the application of the
   art or science to practical purposes. Thus we speak of the skill of a
   mathematician, of a surveyor, of a physician or surgeon, of a mechanic
   or seaman. So we speak of skill in management or negotiation.

   2. Any particular art.
